"(1)  \nThe Vessel’s glass-and-steel spire glittered under the mid-June sun like a broken prism promising nothing but fragments of sky, and on June 14, 2025, the crowd’s restless hum thrummed through the open lobby as Scarlett Thomas stepped onto the dais. A hush slid over the audience of three hundred faces—some expectant, some anxious—while the soft scent of coffee and the electric tang of rain-soaked city air mingled with anticipation. She carried herself with that same careful gravity she’d spoken of in her interviews, the weight of explanation pressing on her chest as she was introduced, her voice steady but edged with the unspoken awareness of how stories end even before the final page. Before her, rows of tables displayed signed copies of her latest novel, their spines cracked and edges worn by eager hands, while her words—meant to illuminate her craft—echoed faintly in the chamber of the Vessel at Hudson Yards, a place of both promise and inevitable decay."